JOHANNESBURG The Broad-Based Black Economic Empowerment Commission has initiated an investigation into Netcare, Nokia, MTN, Eskom, and the South African Social Security Agency for allegedly violating the Act that governs economic empowerment.According to the commission, it' i investigating MTN s broad-based black economic empowerment schemes.WATCH: Competition Commission denies it's letting banks offIt is investigating Nokia Solutions and Networks SA to determine whether a triple BEE ownership transaction involving its employee trust and Sekunjalo Investment complied with the law.Entities found to have violated the Act may be referred for prosecution and fined up to 10 percent of its annual turnover.eNCA